title: Grateful Dead Live at Providence Civic Center on 1979-11-04
lineage: Dat (Sony PCM-R500) > Tascam DA-3000 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, Easy To Love You, Brown Eyed Women, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal

Set 2

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: wow wow wow Stellar performance, great recording.

Providence 79...My first hometown show? This may or may not have been my first hometown show when I was 16 as they played Providence Jan 18, 79 that same year so could have been that show with Donna and Keith also? Whichever one it was I remember this fully naked girl who was probably tripping balls leaped from the barrier onto the stage during intermission landing hard on her shins then stood a bit frazzled and flashed the crowd the peace sign before getting carried off by the roadies. First time Alabama and The Phil Bombs on The Other One are over the top!! ha
